node.text:
❓ What’s your favorite land in Magic Kingdom?

💡 The backstory of Tomorrowland is that it’s an intergalactic space port and functions as a full working city. One important part of this relates to the metallic palm trees that can be seen in the back of this photo.

🌴 They’re called Power Palms and were developed by the Tomorrowland Power Company. They were created to capture energy from the sun, which is then stored in coconut-shaped globes that hang from the trees. When the globes are full, the Power Company harvests them and uses the energy to power Tomorrowland!

👀 Keep your eyes out for one Power Palm in Tomorrowland that’s all folded up and doesn’t have any coconuts. This is because the power from that tree has already been harvested!
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓ What’s your favorite dessert to eat on Disney property?

📸 DISNEY DESSERT FOOD REVIEW! The past few trips we’ve tried so many different desserts (these pictures don’t even cover them all). See below for some of our reviews and recommendations!

1️⃣ Num Num Cookie from Municiberg: A must-try and perfect for sharing. 10/10

2️⃣ Churros and chocolate dip from Pecos Bill: First time trying this but a classic Disney churro. 8.5/10

3️⃣ Vegan ice cream from Boardwalk Ice Cream: I love finding vegan options in the parks and this did not disappoint! 9/10 

4️⃣ Cheshire Cat Tail from Lunching Pad: Another one of our go-to’s, simple but delicious. 9.5/10

5️⃣ Local Wildflower Honey-Mascarpone Cheesecake from The Honey Bee-stro: Delicious, refreshing, and very light! 9/10

6️⃣ Fried Cinnamon Roll Bites from Sunshine Griddle: Doughy and an amazing breakfast treat. 9/10

7️⃣ Pecan Pie from Flower and Garden Festival: Really good sauce and whipped cream but a little dry. 8/10 

8️⃣Ooey Gooey Toffee Cake from Liberty Tree Tavern: Amazing in every way (except I’m very lactose intolerant hahah). 10/10

9️⃣ Lemon Cake with Strawberries from Hollywood and Vine: Sadly a bit disappointing, didn’t love any desserts here.  5/10 

🔟 Cinnamon Bun from Gaston’s Tavern: Perfect for sharing, be sure to ask for the extra free icing! 8/10
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓How old were you when you first rode Tower of Terror? We never did it as kids and only tried it in our early teen years!
 
⚡️ This fact about the Tower of Terror might shock you. The screams you hear while waiting in line? Most of them are prerecorded!

🌀 While there are many screams that are real, Disney doesn’t pipe them into the queue. You never know what guests will say, and the screams Disney chose definitely set the mood for the ride!
.
. 
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓Have you ever done a tour at Disney? Let us know which in the comments! 
 
🌐In 2019 we did the UnDISCOVERed Future World tour at Epcot. This tour took us through all the future world pavilions - we learned the history, cut the line to do the rides, and got to go in many of the private lounges! We also went backstage Epcot which was awesome. 

📷 One of the coolest things we got to do was hold a piece of a dinosaur animatronic from Ellen’s Universe of Energy, and see a bunch of behind the scenes photos! 

➡️Swipe to see pictures!!
.
. 
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓Have you ever eaten at Woody’s Lunch Box in Toy Story Land? What’s your go-to order? 

🤠 Next time you walk through Toy Story Land, look for the giant cereal box of Lass-O’s. At the top, you’ll see Battle Creek listed. 

🥣 This is actually a tribute to Battle Creek, Michigan, where Kellogg’s cereal brand was founded! We absolutely love these clever details the Imagineers leave in the parks. 
.
. 
.
.
.
.
@wdwnt

node.text:
❓Should Rock’n’Rollercoaster change the band from Aerosmith to someone else? Let us know in the comments!

🎵 Here’s a fun fact about Rock’n’Rollercoaster! While waiting in the area near the studios, guests can overhear several different announcements paging certain artists and workers to report to different areas. 

🎸 Guests who listen closely might pick up on a great reference which pays tribute to one of the biggest bands in the history of rock and roll. The page is looking for an employee named Jude and features the phrase “hey, Jude!” which pays homage to the iconic Beatles song of the same name.
.
. 
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓If you could spend the night in one Disney park, which would you pick? Let us know in the comments!

🛌 Did you know there was almost a hotel on Main Street USA? Conceptual plans for Magic Kingdom once called for a hotel where the Town Square Theater is today. 

🪟 There are facade balconies built, but the second story would have been rooms for guests! The inside lobby also would have contained a second story. 

.
. 
.
.
.
.

❓When is your next Disney trip? Let us know in the comments!

🏰 Surprise!! We booked another trip to Disney for Labor Day weekend!! We are beyond excited to have added an extra trip this year, and we have so much planned. 

🛏 We are staying deluxe for the second time ever at Saratoga Springs! We’ll be sharing later how to make staying deluxe actually be affordable 

🐀 We have a Passholder preview for the Ratatouille ride!

🐬 We’re also going to Discovery Cove to swim with the dolphins!!

🏰 We can’t wait to share more trip details with you guys, and give you some of the tips for how we made this possible!
.
. 
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓Are you excited for the new Ratatouille ride to open soon? Let us know in the comments!

🐁 We got a spot for the Ratatouille ride Passholder preview in September!! This is one of our all time favorite Disney rides - we’ve done it in Disneyland Paris and can’t wait for our sneak peek!

🎢This ride is a trackless ride, sort of like Mickey & Minnie’s Runaway Railway! You’ll be shrunk down to the size of a rat and taken through a bunch of scenes from the movie. It’s such an incredible ride, we can’t wait for it to open at Epcot!
.
. 
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓ Today we’re playing MYTH or FACT! For each of the statements below, decide if you think it’s a Myth or a Fact and add your answers to the comments. Then check our story to see how you did!

1️⃣ Cinderella Castle can be partially dismantled during hurricanes to avoid damage to the turrets.
 
2️⃣ The clock on Cinderella Castle always sits pointed to just before midnight to signify that in the Magic Kingdom, the magic never ends.

3️⃣ After the tourism drop due to 9/11, Disney abandoned half of the Pop Century resort for nearly 10 years.

4️⃣ During the creation of Magic Kingdom, three resorts were planned for the monorail loop that ultimately were never built: the Asian Resort, the Persian Resort, and the Venetian Resort.

5️⃣ The rooms at the Contemporary hotel were built so that they could later be removed, updated, and then slid back into place. However, due to the way the land settled, this was never actually used and the rooms can no longer be removed.

6️⃣ The dolls in It’s A Small World have to be given annual haircuts due to the way their yarn hair stretches.

7️⃣ Tower of Terror is not quite centered on Sunset Boulevard because its location had to be moved at the last minute due to a sinkhole.

8️⃣ A Cast Member controls the spitting camel in Adventureland by watching through a hidden camera and pressing a button to spray water when guests are properly positioned to get wet.

9️⃣ There are five Haunted Mansions across the Disney parks around the world, but no two are located within the same land.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
❓ What ride vehicle do you find most uncomfortable at Disney? Let us know in the comments!
 
🎢 My top 3 are Astro Orbiter (it’s hard to get in and out of), Space Mountain (my long legs struggle with that one) and Seven Dwarves Mine Train (the seats are so small!)

⛰ Did you know that Asia was considered the first expansion of Animal Kingdom? Even after it opened, it only contained two attractions: Flights of Wonder and the Discovery River Boats Upcountry Landing. 

⛲️Kali River Rapids was still under construction when the land opened, with an opening date of March 18, 1999. Everest didn’t open until years later in April 7, 2006!
.
.
.
.
.
